                  <h3 class="fw-bold mb-4 text-center">Health Guidelines for Male</h3>
  
                  <p>A person’s lifestyle influences how healthy they are. 
                      The following poor health risk factors are likely to occur for male: smoking tobacco, 
                      alcohol consumption, overweight, dont eat much friut and vegatables. 
                  </p>

                  <p class="mb-2"><strong>Fun Fact of Male:</strong></p>
                  <!-- icons below could be ticks or crosses or exercise icons https://mdbootstrap.com/docs/standard/content-styles/icons/ -->
                  <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li><i class="fas fa-hand-point-right me-2"></i>3 in 4 men were overweight or obese in 2017–18</li>
                  <li><i class="fas fa-hand-point-right me-2"></i>In 2017-2018, fewer than 1 in 30 men ate required amount of fruit and vegatables.</li>
                  </ul>
  
                  <p class="mb-2"><strong>How to stay healthy:</strong></p>
                  <!-- icons below could be ticks or crosses or exercise icons https://mdbootstrap.com/docs/standard/content-styles/icons/ -->
                  <ul class="list-unstyled">
                  <li><i class="fas fa-utensils me-2"></i>Eat 6 serves of vegetables and fruit in different type and colour</li>
                  <li><i class="fas fa-person-walking me-2"></i>5 hours moderate intensity physical activity each week</li>
                  <li><i class="fas fa-person-walking me-2"></i>2.5 hours of vigorous intensity physical activity each week</li>
                  <li><i class="fas fa-check text-success me-2"></i>Check in with your local GP</li>
                  <li><i class="fas fa-xmark text-danger me-2"></i>Don't siting or lying down all day</li>
                  </ul>
                  <div class="btn-group shadow-0" role="group" aria-label="Guidelines and Information">
                  <a class="btn btn-outline-secondary" href="https://www.aihw.gov.au/reports/men-women/male-health/contents/lifestyle-and-risk-factors/diet" role="button" data-mdb-ripple-color="primary">Australian male diet guidelines</a>
